author: Irene Klotz
description: A pair of astronauts will venture outside the International Space Station on Tuesday for an emergency spacewalk to replace a failed computer, one of two that control major U.S. systems aboard the orbiting outpost, NASA said on Sunday.
title: NASA plans emergency spacewalk on International Space Station

description: Freeze-dried sperm that was stored in space aboard the International Space Station for nine months has been used to produce healthy mouse pups on Earth.
title: 'Space pups' bred on Earth from mouse sperm stored on ISS

description: A pair of astronauts will venture outside the International Space Station for an emergency spacewalk to replace a failed computer, NASA says.
title: NASA plans emergency spacewalk on ISS

author: Irene Klotz, Reuters
description: The device helps control solar power system, radiators, cooling loops, and other equipment on the International Space Station'
title: A critical computer has failed on NASA's $100 billion space station and astronauts are gearing up for emergency repairs

author: James Dean
description: Astronauts aboard international space station will replace a data relay box that failed May 20, 2017.
